WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.953 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.953 --> 00:00:04.145 align:middle line:90%
-Hey, it's me.

00:00:04.145 --> 00:00:05.566 align:middle line:90%
I'm the one that got fired.

00:00:05.566 --> 00:00:06.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm gone.

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:07.640 align:middle line:90%
You don't know that.

00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:08.855 align:middle line:90%
But what if it is?

00:00:08.855 --> 00:00:10.270 align:middle line:90%
If it is, stay calm.

00:00:10.270 --> 00:00:13.321 align:middle line:84%
Look him straight in the
eye and say, I understand.

00:00:13.321 --> 00:00:14.020 align:middle line:90%
Be a man.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:15.260 align:middle line:84%
Something good
will come from it.

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:19.730 align:middle line:84%
Michael, Mr. Kendrick
wants to see you.

00:00:19.730 --> 00:00:21.207 align:middle line:84%
Pete is a great
worker, and he's really

00:00:21.207 --> 00:00:22.240 align:middle line:90%
afraid he's going to get fired.

00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:23.860 align:middle line:84%
And he's an excellent
worker, you know.

00:00:23.860 --> 00:00:26.150 align:middle line:90%
OK, Michael, I'm sorry.

00:00:26.150 --> 00:00:29.010 align:middle line:84%
I know you've been
with us for 14 years,

00:00:29.010 --> 00:00:30.985 align:middle line:84%
but we are going to
have to let you go.

00:00:30.985 --> 00:00:38.680 align:middle line:90%


00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:39.672 align:middle line:90%
I understand.

00:00:39.672 --> 00:00:53.560 align:middle line:90%


00:00:53.560 --> 00:00:55.560 align:middle line:84%
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:57.931 align:middle line:84%
Whoa, I thought-- I thought
I had five months to pay.

00:00:57.931 --> 00:00:59.730 align:middle line:84%
Pay your mortgage.
That's all I got to say.

00:00:59.730 --> 00:01:00.830 align:middle line:90%
That's all you got for me?

00:01:00.830 --> 00:01:02.090 align:middle line:90%
That's all I got to say to you.

00:01:02.090 --> 00:01:03.391 align:middle line:84%
Thanks Mr. Empathy.
MAN: That's right.

00:01:03.391 --> 00:01:04.089 align:middle line:90%
Appreciate it.

00:01:04.089 --> 00:01:05.300 align:middle line:84%
And if you touch
the sign, there's

00:01:05.300 --> 00:01:06.314 align:middle line:90%
going to be a problem here.

00:01:06.314 --> 00:01:07.780 align:middle line:84%
Oh, there's going to
be a problem from you?

00:01:07.780 --> 00:01:09.200 align:middle line:84%
-That's right.
-What if I don't touch the sign?

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:10.450 align:middle line:84%
What if I'm this close?
-Don't touch it.

00:01:10.450 --> 00:01:11.149 align:middle line:90%
What about this?

00:01:11.149 --> 00:01:12.390 align:middle line:84%
Does that mess
with your universe?

00:01:12.390 --> 00:01:13.150 align:middle line:90%
Pretty close.

00:01:13.150 --> 00:01:16.200 align:middle line:84%
You know, just trespassing.
Go, shoo.

00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:19.700 align:middle line:90%


00:01:19.700 --> 00:01:41.501 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I just posted 222.

00:01:41.501 --> 00:01:43.950 align:middle line:84%
It's natural to feel
frustrated from time to time.

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:46.075 align:middle line:84%
Even the best of us get caught
up in negative emotions.

00:01:46.075 --> 00:01:48.540 align:middle line:84%
It's even more important
not to get down on yourself

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:50.180 align:middle line:84%
for getting angry, because
then more than likely,

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:52.210 align:middle line:84%
you're going to project
that anger out onto others,

00:01:52.210 --> 00:01:53.340 align:middle line:90%
even people you love.

00:01:53.340 --> 00:02:01.477 align:middle line:90%


00:02:01.477 --> 00:02:02.810 align:middle line:84%
You know, we're going
to try the summer

00:02:02.810 --> 00:02:04.245 align:middle line:90%
lobster dinner for two.

00:02:04.245 --> 00:02:05.050 align:middle line:90%
Sounds terrific.

00:02:05.050 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:90%
And that's just for me.

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.470 align:middle line:90%
No it's not.

00:02:07.470 --> 00:02:11.009 align:middle line:84%
The key is to realign with
your original, authentic passion

00:02:11.009 --> 00:02:13.510 align:middle line:84%
and then commit to it, and
don't accept anything that

00:02:13.510 --> 00:02:15.030 align:middle line:90%
doesn't support the real you.

00:02:15.030 --> 00:02:16.679 align:middle line:84%
-So it's movie night.
-Yes.

00:02:16.679 --> 00:02:18.390 align:middle line:84%
And I know you wanted
to see "The Captain

00:02:18.390 --> 00:02:19.220 align:middle line:90%
of the World" movie.

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:19.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no, no.

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:22.491 align:middle line:84%
Honey, it's-- it's
"Captain America."

00:02:22.491 --> 00:02:23.190 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:02:23.190 --> 00:02:26.530 align:middle line:84%
But there's a movie at the Kino
called "The Keeper of the Keys"

00:02:26.530 --> 00:02:28.547 align:middle line:84%
that I really wanted
to see together.

00:02:28.547 --> 00:02:29.280 align:middle line:90%
"Keeper of the Keys."

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Is that the new Nick Cage film?
-No.

00:02:31.910 --> 00:02:36.745 align:middle line:84%
It's a documentary about seven
keys that can change your life.

00:02:36.745 --> 00:02:39.860 align:middle line:90%
Ooh, no, no, no, no.

00:02:39.860 --> 00:02:41.720 align:middle line:84%
Honey, one of those talking
head transformational

00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:43.700 align:middle line:84%
documentaries about how
to make a better life?

00:02:43.700 --> 00:02:47.067 align:middle line:84%
I don't-- ah-- I don't think
I can see that on movie night.

00:02:47.067 --> 00:02:48.200 align:middle line:84%
You know, I think
I'd rather shoot

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:50.200 align:middle line:84%
myself in the head with a rubber
bullet than see that movie.

00:02:50.200 --> 00:02:51.670 align:middle line:90%
Ooh, a negative reaction.

00:02:51.670 --> 00:02:53.831 align:middle line:90%
What a surprise.

00:02:53.831 --> 00:02:55.065 align:middle line:90%
What's that supposed to mean?

00:02:55.065 --> 00:02:57.450 align:middle line:84%
It means that every
time I've tried

00:02:57.450 --> 00:02:59.320 align:middle line:84%
to bring something new
to our relationship,

00:02:59.320 --> 00:03:00.600 align:middle line:90%
you make fun of me.

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:01.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm sorry,
but I don't think

00:03:01.960 --> 00:03:03.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm alone when I
say there have been

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:05.240 align:middle line:84%
countless books and
movies all claiming

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:06.220 align:middle line:90%
to have the secret to life.

00:03:06.220 --> 00:03:07.453 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you got "The
Four Contracts,"

00:03:07.453 --> 00:03:09.220 align:middle line:84%
"The Seven Positive Laws,"
"The Nine Prerogatives."

00:03:09.220 --> 00:03:11.086 align:middle line:84%
You know the guy who wrote
"The Nine Prerogatives" lives

00:03:11.086 --> 00:03:12.860 align:middle line:84%
in a hut on a beach in Kauai?
-Sounds amazing.

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:14.354 align:middle line:90%
He has no adversity whatsoever.

00:03:14.354 --> 00:03:15.620 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't need all
nine prerogatives.

00:03:15.620 --> 00:03:17.490 align:middle line:84%
He'd get along
with three or four.

00:03:17.490 --> 00:03:18.347 align:middle line:90%
I'd need, like, 11.

00:03:18.347 --> 00:03:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And then years later, a
new edition comes out.

00:03:19.880 --> 00:03:22.840 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly there's five contracts,
there's eight positive laws.

00:03:22.840 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
What about the poor sucker
who bought the first edition?

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:25.930 align:middle line:90%
What, he's kind of enlightened?

00:03:25.930 --> 00:03:26.930 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm going to do?

00:03:26.930 --> 00:03:28.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to write my
own self-help book.

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:29.530 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
called the one and only

00:03:29.530 --> 00:03:31.670 align:middle line:84%
ultimate book of enlightenment
that you ever need ever.

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:32.450 align:middle line:84%
-Oh yeah?
-Yeah.

00:03:32.450 --> 00:03:33.870 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be 750 pages long.

00:03:33.870 --> 00:03:36.790 align:middle line:84%
Page one, it's going to say
do what you can then stop.

00:03:36.790 --> 00:03:38.461 align:middle line:90%
The rest will be totally blank.

00:03:38.461 --> 00:03:49.754 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.754 --> 00:03:50.720 align:middle line:90%
Flowers, flowers.

00:03:50.720 --> 00:03:54.320 align:middle line:90%


00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:55.570 align:middle line:90%
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:03:55.570 --> 00:03:57.109 align:middle line:84%
Stop, stop, stop.
Please, I'm sorry.

00:03:57.109 --> 00:03:57.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm really sorry.

00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:58.819 align:middle line:90%
I know I'm negative sometimes.

00:03:58.819 --> 00:04:02.650 align:middle line:84%
I had these hidden behind
the-- just take them.

00:04:02.650 --> 00:04:03.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:04:03.460 --> 00:04:09.520 align:middle line:90%


00:04:09.520 --> 00:04:12.110 align:middle line:84%
Only works if you
really mean it, man.

00:04:12.110 --> 00:04:13.920 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Dr. Phil.

00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:16.490 align:middle line:90%
Can I keep these?

00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:17.620 align:middle line:90%
No, you can't keep them.

00:04:17.620 --> 00:04:21.540 align:middle line:90%


00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:23.500 align:middle line:90%
[GROAN]

00:04:23.500 --> 00:04:31.830 align:middle line:90%


00:04:31.830 --> 00:04:33.550 align:middle line:84%
I need to be with
somebody who's not negative

00:04:33.550 --> 00:04:34.470 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:04:34.470 --> 00:04:36.309 align:middle line:84%
Oh, now I'm negative
all the time.

00:04:36.309 --> 00:04:37.075 align:middle line:90%
That's just ridiculous.

00:04:37.075 --> 00:04:40.380 align:middle line:90%


00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:41.550 align:middle line:90%
My painting.

00:04:41.550 --> 00:04:43.360 align:middle line:90%
Wow, is that Anne's too?

00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:44.580 align:middle line:90%
Yes it is.

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:45.940 align:middle line:90%
Has she sold any yet?

00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:47.165 align:middle line:90%
Like to who, a therapist?

00:04:47.165 --> 00:04:50.320 align:middle line:84%
They can use it as
a Rorschach test.

00:04:50.320 --> 00:04:51.540 align:middle line:90%
I see a bunny.

00:04:51.540 --> 00:04:53.580 align:middle line:90%
I see a wilting tornado.

00:04:53.580 --> 00:04:54.710 align:middle line:90%
I see disco parsley.

00:04:54.710 --> 00:04:58.590 align:middle line:90%


00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:00.270 align:middle line:84%
You hear something?
-No.

00:05:00.270 --> 00:05:01.310 align:middle line:90%
What are you looking at?

00:05:01.310 --> 00:05:02.116 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:05:02.116 --> 00:05:03.320 align:middle line:84%
Look, that was
just me projecting

00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:04.780 align:middle line:90%
my own ignorance outward, OK.

00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:07.499 align:middle line:84%
I know nothing
about art, nothing.

00:05:07.499 --> 00:05:08.465 align:middle line:90%
It hurt.

00:05:08.465 --> 00:05:14.261 align:middle line:90%


00:05:14.261 --> 00:05:15.842 align:middle line:90%
I wish you the best.

00:05:15.842 --> 00:05:34.050 align:middle line:90%


00:05:34.050 --> 00:05:35.280 align:middle line:84%
Write down every
negative thought

00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:39.165 align:middle line:84%
you've had in the last year.
I dare you.

00:05:39.165 --> 00:05:43.776 align:middle line:90%


00:05:43.776 --> 00:05:45.330 align:middle line:90%
Well see, that's funny.

00:05:45.330 --> 00:05:46.901 align:middle line:90%
That's incorrect, but funny.

00:05:46.901 --> 00:05:49.550 align:middle line:90%


00:05:49.550 --> 00:05:52.340 align:middle line:84%
Hey, if you're going, take your
damn Rorschach test with you.

00:05:52.340 --> 00:05:57.189 align:middle line:90%


00:05:57.189 --> 00:05:59.544 align:middle line:84%
God damn it.
Fine.

00:05:59.544 --> 00:06:01.091 align:middle line:84%
I'm keeping it.
I'm keeping it.

00:06:01.091 --> 00:06:01.790 align:middle line:90%
It's mine now.

00:06:01.790 --> 00:06:05.010 align:middle line:90%


00:06:05.010 --> 00:06:06.390 align:middle line:90%
Oh, just fine.

00:06:06.390 --> 00:06:07.960 align:middle line:90%
Just--

00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:09.940 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:09.940 --> 00:06:21.684 align:middle line:90%


00:06:21.684 --> 00:06:23.050 align:middle line:84%
All right, there may
have been one or two

00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:26.010 align:middle line:90%
moments that were not my best.

00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:28.196 align:middle line:84%
"Dead Poets Society"
is in your top 10?

00:06:28.196 --> 00:06:29.590 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it's like my top two.

00:06:29.590 --> 00:06:32.600 align:middle line:84%
Excuse me, how could you not
like "Dead Poets Society"?

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.030 align:middle line:84%
Because the whole seize the
day thing, seize the day,

00:06:35.030 --> 00:06:37.000 align:middle line:84%
seize the day, carpe
diem, it was on bumper

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:37.910 align:middle line:90%
stickers and t-shirts.

00:06:37.910 --> 00:06:39.070 align:middle line:84%
Ever since I saw
that movie, I've

00:06:39.070 --> 00:06:40.480 align:middle line:84%
been working my
ass off terrified

00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:42.436 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't seizing the damn day.

00:06:42.436 --> 00:06:44.910 align:middle line:84%
-The classroom scene?
-Yeah.

00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:46.051 align:middle line:84%
Made me a workaholic.
Thank you.

00:06:46.051 --> 00:06:47.671 align:middle line:84%
Are you happy?
---a ticket here.

00:06:47.671 --> 00:06:49.070 align:middle line:84%
This is all you have
to do with your life

00:06:49.070 --> 00:06:51.210 align:middle line:84%
is to site me for
being 29 inches

00:06:51.210 --> 00:06:52.940 align:middle line:84%
from the curb instead of 18.
That's it.

00:06:52.940 --> 00:06:53.795 align:middle line:90%
That's all you got.

00:06:53.795 --> 00:06:55.595 align:middle line:84%
Look, I don't want any more
of this from you, mister.

00:06:55.595 --> 00:06:58.141 align:middle line:84%
You want me take you downtown,
because that's the next step?

00:06:58.141 --> 00:06:58.840 align:middle line:90%
You like that?

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:00.007 align:middle line:84%
If I have to go
anywhere with you,

00:07:00.007 --> 00:07:01.006 align:middle line:90%
I'm just going to kill myself.

00:07:01.006 --> 00:07:02.700 align:middle line:84%
I can take you right
downtown, and you can spend

00:07:02.700 --> 00:07:05.010 align:middle line:84%
24 to 48 hours in the jail.
You want that?

00:07:05.010 --> 00:07:07.120 align:middle line:84%
I'd rather smack myself in
the face with a wet spatula

00:07:07.120 --> 00:07:08.370 align:middle line:90%
than spend time with you.

00:07:08.370 --> 00:07:11.060 align:middle line:84%
You need some work
on how to drive,

00:07:11.060 --> 00:07:12.610 align:middle line:84%
on how to deal with
the city officials.

00:07:12.610 --> 00:07:13.370 align:middle line:90%
Please counsel me.

00:07:13.370 --> 00:07:14.670 align:middle line:84%
Please, give me all
the advice you can.

00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:15.907 align:middle line:84%
I'm really going
to listen to you.

00:07:15.907 --> 00:07:17.430 align:middle line:84%
-Sir, just take your violation.
-You especially.

00:07:17.430 --> 00:07:18.463 align:middle line:90%
Sir, just take your violation.

00:07:18.463 --> 00:07:20.742 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to
soak it up like--

00:07:20.742 --> 00:07:22.385 align:middle line:84%
"A Christmas Carol" is
your favorite movie.

00:07:22.385 --> 00:07:24.620 align:middle line:84%
What's not to love about
"A Christmas Carol"?

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:26.640 align:middle line:90%
Because the end is criminal.

00:07:26.640 --> 00:07:27.530 align:middle line:90%
It's criminal.

00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:29.640 align:middle line:84%
Everyone goes oh,
Scrooge had an awakening.

00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:31.380 align:middle line:84%
I should be able to muster one.
Well you know what?

00:07:31.380 --> 00:07:32.360 align:middle line:90%
Scrooge was rich.

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:33.990 align:middle line:90%
He was ravenously rich.

00:07:33.990 --> 00:07:35.370 align:middle line:84%
No wonder it was so
easy for him to flip

00:07:35.370 --> 00:07:36.770 align:middle line:90%
a switch into Happyville.

00:07:36.770 --> 00:07:38.660 align:middle line:90%
The man was freaking loaded.

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:42.510 align:middle line:84%
(MOCKING) You will be
visited by three ghosts.

00:07:42.510 --> 00:07:43.370 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:07:43.370 --> 00:07:44.973 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:07:44.973 --> 00:07:46.270 align:middle line:90%
How can you not love it?

00:07:46.270 --> 00:07:47.375 align:middle line:90%
Jacob Marley.

00:07:47.375 --> 00:07:48.350 align:middle line:90%
Or is it Bob Marley?

00:07:48.350 --> 00:07:50.620 align:middle line:84%
It's not about--
it's not about that.

00:07:50.620 --> 00:07:51.650 align:middle line:90%
The ghost of Bob Marley.

00:07:51.650 --> 00:07:52.617 align:middle line:90%
That's a film I would see.

00:07:52.617 --> 00:07:55.060 align:middle line:90%


00:07:55.060 --> 00:07:56.660 align:middle line:84%
JACK (VOICEOVER): I know
you feel like a victim,

00:07:56.660 --> 00:07:58.310 align:middle line:84%
but the only thing
you're a victim of

00:07:58.310 --> 00:07:59.780 align:middle line:90%
is your own negative thinking.

00:07:59.780 --> 00:08:01.385 align:middle line:84%
You know Michael, you can
run from your problems

00:08:01.385 --> 00:08:04.540 align:middle line:84%
and you can mask them with
alcohol and drugs and all kinds

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:06.940 align:middle line:84%
of activity, but when you
wake up in the morning,

00:08:06.940 --> 00:08:08.900 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be hung
over and your problems

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:11.440 align:middle line:84%
are still going to be
there, (ECHOING) be there.

00:08:11.440 --> 00:08:12.615 align:middle line:90%
Are you talking to me?

00:08:12.615 --> 00:08:13.910 align:middle line:90%
Well of course I am.

00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:15.180 align:middle line:90%
Whoa.

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:17.565 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to send some friends
to you, and they're experts,

00:08:17.565 --> 00:08:20.240 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to show
you how to use the keys.

00:08:20.240 --> 00:08:20.980 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:08:20.980 --> 00:08:22.410 align:middle line:84%
You know what the
keys are, right?

00:08:22.410 --> 00:08:31.230 align:middle line:90%


00:08:31.230 --> 00:08:33.190 align:middle line:90%
[DOORBELL RINGING]

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:36.980 align:middle line:90%


00:08:36.980 --> 00:08:38.419 align:middle line:90%
Hi, I'm Elizabeth.

00:08:38.419 --> 00:08:40.320 align:middle line:84%
I got your message.
