00:17:53.020 --> 00:17:55.340 align:middle line:84%
And you probably feel
you're just being yourself.

00:17:55.340 --> 00:17:57.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, for that person,
you're too negative.

00:17:57.460 --> 00:17:59.610 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe you might
think, well, everybody's

00:17:59.610 --> 00:18:00.990 align:middle line:84%
going to think
you're too negative,

00:18:00.990 --> 00:18:02.720 align:middle line:84%
and then you have to
make some adjustments.

00:18:02.720 --> 00:18:04.450 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
adjust who you are.

00:18:04.450 --> 00:18:07.480 align:middle line:84%
You have to adjust how you
communicate who you are.

00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:08.990 align:middle line:84%
When you feel angry
inside, you have

00:18:08.990 --> 00:18:11.470 align:middle line:84%
to realize if you express
that anger to someone,

00:18:11.470 --> 00:18:13.000 align:middle line:90%
they'll take it as rejection.

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:14.330 align:middle line:90%
They may become afraid.

00:18:14.330 --> 00:18:15.480 align:middle line:90%
They may feel abandoned.

00:18:15.480 --> 00:18:17.040 align:middle line:90%
They may be scared.

00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:18.970 align:middle line:84%
You don't know what reaction
you're having, but if you're

00:18:18.970 --> 00:18:21.770 align:middle line:84%
getting a negative reaction
to expressing your anger,

00:18:21.770 --> 00:18:24.050 align:middle line:84%
then you need to learn how
to express it in a way that

00:18:24.050 --> 00:18:25.640 align:middle line:90%
doesn't create that reaction.

00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:28.290 align:middle line:84%
You can be angry, but
how do you communicate

00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:29.980 align:middle line:90%
how you feel to another person?

00:18:29.980 --> 00:18:31.650 align:middle line:84%
In terms of rebuilding
a relationship,

00:18:31.650 --> 00:18:32.950 align:middle line:90%
there may be no chance.

00:18:32.950 --> 00:18:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Once you've lost trust, it's
often hard to rebuild it.

00:18:35.730 --> 00:18:37.410 align:middle line:90%
It does happen, though.

00:18:37.410 --> 00:18:40.140 align:middle line:84%
If you can look and do an
inventory of yourself--

00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:43.880 align:middle line:84%
how have I contributed to the
problems in this relationship,

00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:46.640 align:middle line:84%
how have I not heard my
partner-- that doesn't

00:18:46.640 --> 00:18:48.260 align:middle line:90%
mean you're completely wrong.

00:18:48.260 --> 00:18:50.350 align:middle line:84%
There's always two
sides to every issue.

00:18:50.350 --> 00:18:52.400 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to
take responsibility

00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:55.320 align:middle line:84%
to attract her back, to
create that relationship,

00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:57.770 align:middle line:84%
or to create a better
relationship in the future,

00:18:57.770 --> 00:19:01.160 align:middle line:84%
you have to look at how you
communicated what you feel

00:19:01.160 --> 00:19:03.310 align:middle line:84%
and the absence of
your positive feelings.

00:19:03.310 --> 00:19:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Look at how to communicate
your positive feelings.

00:19:05.770 --> 00:19:07.610 align:middle line:84%
That's going to draw
the best in another.

