00:20:00.850 --> 00:20:03.680 align:middle line:90%
I was failing in my business.

00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:06.020 align:middle line:84%
Most importantly, I was missing
all the time with my wife

00:20:06.020 --> 00:20:07.280 align:middle line:90%
and with my children.

00:20:07.280 --> 00:20:10.030 align:middle line:84%
And the funny thing is, when
I was spending time with them,

00:20:10.030 --> 00:20:12.030 align:middle line:84%
many years later they
would say to me Dad,

00:20:12.030 --> 00:20:12.970 align:middle line:90%
do you remember this?

00:20:12.970 --> 00:20:14.010 align:middle line:90%
Dad, do you remember that?

00:20:14.010 --> 00:20:16.050 align:middle line:84%
And you said this,
and we said that.

00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:18.460 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't remember,
because even when I did have

00:20:18.460 --> 00:20:20.810 align:middle line:90%
time with them, I wasn't there.

00:20:20.810 --> 00:20:21.727 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't in the room.

00:20:21.727 --> 00:20:23.060 align:middle line:84%
I was somewhere else
thinking about work

00:20:23.060 --> 00:20:24.710 align:middle line:90%
or to pay those bills.

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:27.380 align:middle line:84%
That's the tragedy of
not being your true self.

00:20:27.380 --> 00:20:30.000 align:middle line:84%
When you're your true self, you
can remember all the moments

00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:31.230 align:middle line:90%
and you can have more of them.

00:20:31.230 --> 00:20:32.540 align:middle line:84%
My clients were
running me ragged.

00:20:32.540 --> 00:20:33.380 align:middle line:90%
They were abusing me.

00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:35.525 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one night,
I was so tired

00:20:35.525 --> 00:20:37.500 align:middle line:84%
driving home I
nearly killed myself

00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:38.535 align:middle line:90%
crashing on the motor way.

00:20:38.535 --> 00:20:42.260 align:middle line:84%
And after 18 years in
business, I wasn't depressed,

00:20:42.260 --> 00:20:44.340 align:middle line:90%
but I was clinically unhappy.

00:20:44.340 --> 00:20:45.920 align:middle line:84%
Very late one night,
I'm in my office.

00:20:45.920 --> 00:20:47.960 align:middle line:84%
It's about quarter
to 10:00 at night

00:20:47.960 --> 00:20:50.250 align:middle line:84%
and the security guard came
into the office to lock up,

00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and I said, just give
me 10 more minutes.

00:20:52.060 --> 00:20:55.240 align:middle line:84%
He said, Derek, what time
did you get in this morning?

00:20:55.240 --> 00:20:57.520 align:middle line:84%
I just said, well,
8:00, 8:00 AM.

00:20:57.520 --> 00:21:00.164 align:middle line:84%
And as he walked away, my
words just hung in the air.

00:21:00.164 --> 00:21:01.830 align:middle line:84%
And I put my hand on the
top of the filing cabinet

00:21:01.830 --> 00:21:05.210 align:middle line:84%
and I slammed the door, and
I said, I just had enough,

00:21:05.210 --> 00:21:06.790 align:middle line:84%
and in that moment
is when I changed.

00:21:06.790 --> 00:21:09.320 align:middle line:84%
So immediately, I set
about setting new standards

00:21:09.320 --> 00:21:10.570 align:middle line:90%
for the whole of my life.

00:21:10.570 --> 00:21:13.380 align:middle line:84%
I made a decision to use
the key of appreciation

00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:15.230 align:middle line:84%
and to look at all
areas of my life

00:21:15.230 --> 00:21:17.860 align:middle line:84%
and set new, higher standards
for all of those areas

00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:20.240 align:middle line:84%
and commit to living
at those high standards

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:22.000 align:middle line:90%
from that point onwards.

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:24.420 align:middle line:84%
In England, I'm known
as the standards guy.

00:21:24.420 --> 00:21:26.190 align:middle line:84%
I set really high
standards for myself,

00:21:26.190 --> 00:21:28.480 align:middle line:90%
and I stick at those standards.

00:21:28.480 --> 00:21:31.440 align:middle line:84%
How I changed my life was
that I used to set goals.

00:21:31.440 --> 00:21:33.730 align:middle line:90%
I set goals for 18 years.

00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.330 align:middle line:84%
But until that
night in the office,

00:21:35.330 --> 00:21:37.350 align:middle line:90%
I was a failure on every level.

00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:39.140 align:middle line:84%
See, this guy makes
sense to me because it's

00:21:39.140 --> 00:21:40.360 align:middle line:90%
not some mystical process.

00:21:40.360 --> 00:21:41.490 align:middle line:90%
It's not a five day retreat.

00:21:41.490 --> 00:21:42.760 align:middle line:90%
He just made a decision.

00:21:42.760 --> 00:21:44.350 align:middle line:90%
Bang, it's done.

00:21:44.350 --> 00:21:45.470 align:middle line:90%
That's all it takes.

00:21:45.470 --> 00:21:46.870 align:middle line:90%
I like that.

00:21:46.870 --> 00:21:50.890 align:middle line:84%
When I set standards, my
life changed overnight.

00:21:50.890 --> 00:21:52.965 align:middle line:84%
Within three years, I
become a millionaire.

00:21:52.965 --> 00:21:54.270 align:middle line:90%
(WHISPERING) Millionaire.

00:21:54.270 --> 00:21:58.410 align:middle line:84%
In the following year, I made
$1 million in just that year,

00:21:58.410 --> 00:22:01.240 align:middle line:84%
and I did it by
working half the time.

00:22:01.240 --> 00:22:02.750 align:middle line:84%
You can start by
setting standards

00:22:02.750 --> 00:22:05.100 align:middle line:84%
in all the areas of your life
that you're unhappy with,

00:22:05.100 --> 00:22:09.020 align:middle line:84%
or even angry with, and
decide how you really

00:22:09.020 --> 00:22:10.440 align:middle line:90%
want to feel in those areas.

00:22:10.440 --> 00:22:13.930 align:middle line:84%
And just one day at a time,
just stick at that standard.

00:22:13.930 --> 00:22:15.080 align:middle line:90%
See, it's like a goal.

00:22:15.080 --> 00:22:16.780 align:middle line:84%
We're not saying do this
for the rest of your life.

00:22:16.780 --> 00:22:19.500 align:middle line:84%
Just do it for
today, for one day,

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:20.425 align:middle line:90%
and stick at your standard.

00:22:20.425 --> 00:22:24.110 align:middle line:84%
I got a piece of paper and I
wrote out my weekly timetable,

00:22:24.110 --> 00:22:26.240 align:middle line:84%
and at the start of
every single day,

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:28.995 align:middle line:84%
it would say dad taking
children to school.

00:22:28.995 --> 00:22:30.350 align:middle line:84%
And every day would
finish differently.

00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And three days a week, it
was dad picking children up

00:22:32.190 --> 00:22:35.310 align:middle line:84%
from school and have client
time, non-client time,

00:22:35.310 --> 00:22:37.107 align:middle line:90%
weekends, and family time.

00:22:37.107 --> 00:22:38.340 align:middle line:84%
I worked out this
whole week schedule

00:22:38.340 --> 00:22:41.760 align:middle line:84%
and I actually laminated
it, and I gave one

00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:43.550 align:middle line:84%
to each member of the
family, to each child,

00:22:43.550 --> 00:22:46.620 align:middle line:84%
to my wife, and the last copy,
I put with a fridge magnet

00:22:46.620 --> 00:22:49.580 align:middle line:84%
onto the fridge so everyone
would know this is the new dad.

00:22:49.580 --> 00:22:51.027 align:middle line:90%
This is his new standards.

00:22:51.027 --> 00:22:52.360 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
when you set standards

00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:54.410 align:middle line:84%
is that the people
around you in the world

00:22:54.410 --> 00:22:58.070 align:middle line:84%
will try and judge you or see
you at your old standards.

00:22:58.070 --> 00:23:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And what you have to do
is be patient with them

00:23:00.160 --> 00:23:03.260 align:middle line:84%
and let them know that this is
the new you, the new standards,

00:23:03.260 --> 00:23:05.010 align:middle line:84%
and let them catch up
with where you are.

00:23:05.010 --> 00:23:07.480 align:middle line:84%
Once I set standards,
I discovered

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:09.760 align:middle line:90%
and appreciated my true self.

00:23:09.760 --> 00:23:13.570 align:middle line:90%
And as my true self, I changed.

00:23:13.570 --> 00:23:15.995 align:middle line:84%
And when I changed,
everything changed for me.

